<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-08-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-08-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="671" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d671">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">701.0667/8</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Crosby</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-08-18"><hi rend="italic">August 18,
                                1926</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received September 3.]</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 2035</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: … Referring to the Department’s telegram
                            No. 44 of June 25 regarding the exemption of Diplomatic and Consular
                            officers from the payment of consumption taxes, I have the honor to
                            report that the Foreign Office has recommended favorably to the Council
                            of Ministers the action requested by the Diplomatic Corps. As late as
                            August 9th the Foreign Office had received no reply to its
                            recommendations.</p>
                        <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Sheldon Leavitt
                            Crosby</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>